config SECURITY_PKM
	bool "PKM — Peios Kernel Module"
	depends on SECURITY
	depends on RUST
	depends on !SECURITY_SELINUX
	depends on !SECURITY_APPARMOR
	depends on !SECURITY_SMACK
	depends on !SECURITY_TOMOYO
	help
	  PKM is the Peios Kernel Module, containing:
	  - KACS: Kernel-based Access Control System (tokens, SDs, AccessCheck)
	  - Event subsystem: ring buffer for structured audit events

	  KACS must be the sole MAC LSM. Conflicting MAC LSMs (SELinux,
	  AppArmor, SMACK, TOMOYO) are rejected at Kconfig level.
	  Non-MAC LSMs (landlock, lockdown, yama, integrity) are accepted.

	  If unsure, say N.
